%N A396020 Sum of the distinct prime divisors of C(9*n, n).
%H A396020 Vincenzo Librandi, <a href="/A396020/b396020.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%F A396020 a(n) = sopf(binomial(9*n,n)) = A008472(A169958(n)).
%e A396020 a(2) = 20 because binomial(18,2) = 153 = 3^2*17 and 3+17 = 20.
%e A396020 a(3) = 21 because binomial(27,3) = 2925 = 3^2*5^2*13 and 3+5+13 = 21.
%p A396020 f:= n -> convert(NumberTheory:-PrimeFactors(binomial(9*n,n)),`+`):
%p A396020 map(f, [$1..100]); # _Robert Israel_, May 17 2026
%t A396020 a[n_]:=Total[FactorInteger[Binomial[9*n,n]][[All,1]]]; Table[a[n],{n,1,48}]
%o A396020 (Magma) a := func<n | &+PrimeDivisors(Binomial(9*n, n))>; N := 48; [a(n) : n in [1..N]];
%o A396020 (Python)
%o A396020 from collections import Counter
%o A396020 from sympy import factorint
%o A396020 def A396020(n):
%o A396020     c = Counter()
%o A396020     for i in range(8*n+1,9*n+1):
%o A396020         c += factorint(i)
%o A396020     for i in range(2,n+1):
%o A396020         c -= factorint(i)
%o A396020     return sum(c) # _Chai Wah Wu_, May 17 2026
